  "prompt": "How much import duties would be applied over a clicker worth $2 from U.S.A to India?",
  "response": "The import duties for a $2 clicker from the USA to India can vary depending on several factors such as:\n\n1. Customs classification\n2. Current import regulations\n3. Specific trade agreements\n4. Shipping method\n5. Total package value\n\nFor a low-value item like a $2 clicker, the import duties might be minimal or potentially exempted. However, for a precise calculation, you would need to:\n\n1. Check the exact Harmonized System (HS) code for the item\n2. Consult the current Indian customs tariff\n3. Consider potential additional taxes like GST\n\nGenerally, for such a low-value item:\n- Basic customs duty might be around 10-20%\n- GST could be around 18%\n\nBut for items under a certain value threshold (typically around $20-$50), import duties might be waived.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information, I recommend:\n- Checking with Indian customs authorities\n- Consulting with a customs broker\n- Verifying with the shipping carrier",
